Market Analysis and Insights

Automotive Brake Shoe Market

The rise in the demand for passenger vehicles coupled with the overall rise and expansion of automobile sector, the demand for automotive brake shoe has risen. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the automotive brake shoe market will show a compound annual growth rate of 7.20% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. This when put in terms of market value signifies that the current market value would rise from USD 7,398.30 million to USD 14,827.90 million by the year 2028.

Brake shoe is a part of a vehicle’s brake system that carries the brake lining. It is a curved piece of metal that is incorporated with a friction material fixed to one side. When the brakes are applied, a wheel cylinder in the drum brake system forces the brake shoe in the outward direction against the inside of the drum. This mechanism enables the vehicle to stop or put a halt to the speed. Many get confused and think brake shoes and brake pads are the same things. Their function is same but they are not one and the same things.

Due to rapid expansion of automobile sector, the demand for automotive brake shoes has risen dramatically. Rise in the demand for passenger vehicles incorporated with lightweight frictional materials has also propelled the growth of the market. Rise in the demand for commercialization due to rapid industrialization, modernisation and growth of construction industry has also fostered increase in the market growth rate. Rise in the personal disposable income is another market growth determinant.

However, rising demand for disk brakes in the vehicles will hammer down the automotive brake shoe market growth rate. Overheating of brake shoes and increasing strict regulations pertaining to the heating of brake system will further dampen the growth of automotive brake shoe market.

